==============================================================================
Phase 25 - Orchestrator-side invocation reconstruction (NO live execution)
==============================================================================

The Phase 23 orchestrator invokes (live_linux_lab_orchestrator.sh:2862-2901):

    powershell.exe -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass \
        -File 'C:\Windows\Tempn_bootstrap_windows.ps1' \
        -NodeId '<node_id>' \
        -NetworkId '<NETWORK_ID>' \
        -NodeRole '<role>' \
        -SshAllowCidrs '<SSH_ALLOW_CIDRS>' \
        -SourceArchive 'C:\Windows\Tempustynet_src.tar.gz' \
        -BuildDir 'C:\Windows\Tempn_build' \
        -ServiceName 'RustyNet'

It calls live_lab_ssh "$target" "$invoke_cmd" which becomes:

    ssh -i ~/.ssh/rustynet_lab_ed25519 -o ... -- windows@192.168.65.8 \
        "powershell.exe -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File 'C:\Windows\Temp\rn_bootstrap_windows.ps1' \
         -NodeId 'windows-client-1' ..."

This is PowerShell-over-SSH directly (no cmd.exe wrapper). Per the
Phase 23 reviewer (commit 4a7af92 review), PowerShell-over-SSH fails
with 'Thread failed to start' on memory-pressured Windows hosts; the
workaround documented by the reviewer is to invoke via:

    cmd.exe /c "powershell.exe -EncodedCommand <b64-utf16le>"

The Phase 23 orchestrator does NOT apply that workaround. The wrapper
script is correct but the orchestrator-side invocation does not match
the reviewer's documented compatibility pattern.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Probe: SSH transport itself fails on this VM
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ scp -i ~/.ssh/rustynet_lab_ed25519 ./test windows@192.168.65.8:C:/Windows/Temp/probe.txt
scp: Connection closed

$ ssh -i ~/.ssh/rustynet_lab_ed25519 windows@192.168.65.8 'hostname'

$ ssh -i ~/.ssh/rustynet_lab_ed25519 windows@192.168.65.8 'echo HELLO'
Exception of type 'System.OutOfMemoryException' was thrown.
Thread failed to start.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Inferred root cause
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Windows OpenSSH server uses PowerShell as the default ssh login shell
on Windows 10 (HKLM:\SOFTWARE\OpenSSH\DefaultShell). Every SSH
session bootstraps a PowerShell host before running the command, and
PowerShell host startup loads System.Management.Automation assembly.
With the guest paging file exhausted, the assembly load aborts with
HRESULT 0x800705AF before the command body ever executes.

The orchestrator's Windows arm thus cannot transmit anything to this
VM in its current state - this is a guest-OS-level resource problem,
not a Phase 23/26/27 code defect.

Operator action required:
  1) Open the windows-utm-1 guest console (UTM).
  2) If the guest is logged in: open Task Manager, kill rustynetd.exe
     if it is consuming significant RAM; otherwise sign in and check
     System / Advanced / Performance / Advanced / Virtual memory and
     resize the paging file to 4GB+ (Windows default 'System managed'
     is too small for a 4GB-RAM lab guest under sustained load).
  3) Restart the guest.
  4) Re-run Phase 25 validation from this evidence directory.

